<h2><a name="strlen" id="strlen">strlen</a></h2>
<div class="level2">

<p>
Syntax:
</p>
<pre class="c code c++" style="font-family:monospace;">    <span class="co2">#include &lt;cstring&gt;</span>
    size_t strlen<span class="br0">&#40;</span> <span class="kw4">char</span> <span class="sy0">*</span>str <span class="br0">&#41;</span><span class="sy0">;</span></pre>
<p>

The strlen() function returns the length of str (determined by the number of
characters before null termination). Str may not be null.
</p>

<p>
Related Topics: <a href="memcpy" class="wikilink1" title="c:string:memcpy">memcpy</a>, <a href="strchr" class="wikilink1" title="c:string:strchr">strchr</a>, <a href="strcmp" class="wikilink1" title="c:string:strcmp">strcmp</a>, <a href="strncmp" class="wikilink1" title="c:string:strncmp">strncmp</a>
</p>

